We recommended that the City Government shall endeavor to further improve its tax collection efficiency through the following strategies;

Expedite the completion of the ETRACS; and

The City Assessor shall update the roster of real property taxpayers thru the conduct of field inspections/surveys to identify unregistered/undervalued commercial and residential real properties.

We recommended that Management:

Require the concerned Accountable Officer to submit the accounts and financial reports to the Treasurer and thereafter to submit to the Accounting Office all the disbursements vouchers and payrolls, official receipts, including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the  fifth day of the ensuing month or pursuant to the abovementioned pertinent provisions of laws, rules and regulations, as applicable;

Direct the Accountant to strictly comply with the timelines on the recording and submission of accounts to the Auditor, within the first ten days of the ensuing month, as required by the abovementioned existing law, rules and regulations;

Look into the possibility of augmenting the Accountant’s Office of personnel from other departments, especially during report preparations and/or allowing them to render overtime, subject to availability of funds, in order to submit the accounts and financial reports on the mandated deadlines; and

Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

We recommended that Management:

Appropriate at least five per cent of the total Budget of the Fiscal Year to GAD activities as required in the GAA for the Current Year;

Consider the use of tools (HGDG, PIMME and FIMME) as prescribed PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No. 2016-01 and 2013-01 as aid in planning, budgeting, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of GAD programs and projects;

Develop priority and achievable programs/projects that shall cater to the immediate needs of the target beneficiaries to avoid various unimplemented GAD programs; and 

 Stop the practice of including the payment of honorarium of CHW/BHW, CDW and BNS and other expenses that are not chargeable to the GAD Budget in compliance with the regulations stipulated in the JMC 2016-01.

We also re-iterated our prior year’s audit recommendation that Management guarantee that the GAD plan and budget and GAD accomplishment report shall focus on activities which are geared towards the achievement of the desired outcomes and goals as identified in the Framework Plan for Women.  The priority areas shall be (1) the promotion of gender-responsive governance, (2) protection and fulfillment of women’s human rights; and (3) promotion of women’s economic empowerment.

